==English==
===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}
#{{chemistry}} describing a [[molecule]], such as a [[detergent]], which has both [[hydrophobic]] and [[hydrophilic]] groups.
#{{biochemistry}} often refers to the surface(s) on a protein, particularly an [[alpha helix]], where one surface of the alpha helix has [[hydrophilic]] [[amino acid]]s and the opposite face has [[hydrophobic]] (or [[lipophilic]]) amino acids.

